## Per-User Attribution

Every call to KaixuSI can carry user identity. The worker reads these from the request body first, falls back to headers:

| Body field     | Header equivalent       | What it is |
|----------------|------------------------|------------|
| `user_id`      | `X-Kaixu-User-Id`      | IDE user UUID |
| `workspace_id` | `X-Kaixu-Workspace-Id` | Workspace UUID |
| `org_id`       | `X-Kaixu-Org-Id`       | Org UUID |
| `app_id`       | `X-Kaixu-App`          | Calling app tag |

Every call is logged to `ai_usage_log` in Neon with these fields. This lets you query exactly which user triggered which AI call.

The response always echoes back:
```json
"attributed_to": { "user_id": "...", "workspace_id": "...", "org_id": "...", "app_id": "kaixu-superide" }
```

