## 16. Usage Logging

KaixuSI logs every AI call to `ai_usage_log` in Neon PostgreSQL.

Each row contains:
- `user_id`, `workspace_id`, `org_id`, `app_id` — who made the call
- `provider`, `model` — what was called
- `prompt_tokens`, `completion_tokens` — token counts
- `latency_ms` — response time
- `success` — whether the call succeeded
- `ts` — timestamp

This is logged via `env.ctx.waitUntil()` — fire-and-forget, never delays the response.

Requires `DATABASE_URL` worker secret to be set (Neon PostgreSQL connection string).

